CatDescriptText: A. Andrews, 228 Darraugh Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 8, 1959, pg. B1 with question: "Do you believe the John James Racket Squad is driving the numbers racket out of Pittsburgh?" answer reads: "Actually, I don't know, because I have not read too much about the raids. However, I do not think that the numbers will be driven out, because it has been going on for years."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of A. Andrews, wearing wave and rectangular patterned tie, and dark hat with light colored striped band, posed in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
